[cb8a1ac9-a848-4666-9de5-8fa1283ef594/build]   | Modeling  and  simulation of proton-exchange membrane fuel cells (PEMFC) may work as a powerful tool
[cb8a1ac9-a848-4666-9de5-8fa1283ef594/build]   | in  the  research  &  development of renewable energy sources. The Open-Source PEMFC Simulation Tool
[cb8a1ac9-a848-4666-9de5-8fa1283ef594/build]   | (OPEM)  is  a  modeling  tool for evaluating the performance of proton exchange membrane fuel cells.
[cb8a1ac9-a848-4666-9de5-8fa1283ef594/build]   | This  package  is  a  combination  of  models  (static/dynamic)  that  predict the optimum operating
[cb8a1ac9-a848-4666-9de5-8fa1283ef594/build]   | parameters of PEMFC. OPEM contained generic models that will accept as input, not only values of the
[cb8a1ac9-a848-4666-9de5-8fa1283ef594/build]   | operating  variables such as anode and cathode feed gas, pressure and compositions, cell temperature
[cb8a1ac9-a848-4666-9de5-8fa1283ef594/build]   | and  current  density, but also cell parameters including the active area and membrane thickness. In
[cb8a1ac9-a848-4666-9de5-8fa1283ef594/build]   | addition,  some  of the different models of PEMFC that have been proposed in the OPEM, just focus on
[cb8a1ac9-a848-4666-9de5-8fa1283ef594/build]   | one  particular  FC  stack,  and  some  others  take  into account a part or all auxiliaries such as
[cb8a1ac9-a848-4666-9de5-8fa1283ef594/build]   | reformers. OPEM is a platform for collaborative development of PEMFC models.
